data: Place the Specimen (Airfoil) to be tested in the wing tunnel
Check pressure connections and pressure conditions in the inlet tank.
Align the Airfoil at various angles and take readings
Derive Airfoil Characteristics and determine the Lift generating capabilities and operational range at various angle of attacks.
Don't place bluff bodies in the Mach flow.
Don't release the pressure valve quickly.
Don't remove the ear plugs, ears can get damaged.
Don't place hand or stand towards the exit of wind tunnel.
